    Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2024
    Color: M3 Ultra-Black
    **Smartwatch Review: m3 ultra** This smartwatch is a standout device that brings the robust features of a basic Samsung smartwatch to the table. With its sleek design and impressive functionality, it caters to both tech enthusiasts and fitness fans alike.... See more
    **Smartwatch Review: m3 ultra**

    This smartwatch is a standout device that brings the robust features of a basic Samsung smartwatch to the table. With its sleek design and impressive functionality, it caters to both tech enthusiasts and fitness fans alike.

    **Design and Display:**
    The M3 sports a modern, stylish design that rivals high-end competitors. Its sharp AMOLED display ensures clarity and vibrancy, making it easy to view notifications and watch faces even under direct sunlight. The personalization options for watch faces add a nice touch, allowing users to tailor their experience.

    **Performance and Features:**
    Packed with features, the m3 excels in offering comprehensive health and fitness tracking. Heart rate monitoring, sleep tracking, and GPS capabilities are all included, making it a reliable companion for fitness tracking. The smartwatch mirrors the basic features you'd expect from a Samsung device, providing a familiar and intuitive user experience.

    **Battery Life:**
    Battery performance is impressive, lasting up to 7 days on a single charge under normal usage. This extended battery life is a major advantage, minimizing the hassle of frequent charging.

    **Connectivity and Apps:**
    While the smartwatch offers seamless connectivity with Android and iOS I did notice a slight hiccup with the Bluetooth connection. Occasionally, features like the weather app require manual updates, which can be a minor inconvenience. However, this issue is not a dealbreaker and doesn't significantly detract from the overall experience.

    **Conclusion:**
    In summary, this watch is a fantastic smartwatch that delivers on most fronts. With all the essential features of a basic Samsung smartwatch, it offers great value. Despite the occasional Bluetooth slowdown, particularly with the weather app updates, the overall performance and functionality make it a worthy investment for anyone looking to enhance their tech arsenal.

    Color: Black
    This was the first smart watch, or any watch in 30+ years I have purchased. I got it because though I am in relatively good health, I am no spring chicken anymore. I bought this as a 60th b-day present to myself. I knew I did not want to go super cheap so I chose this one... See more
    This was the first smart watch, or any watch in 30+ years I have purchased. I got it because though I am in relatively good health, I am no spring chicken anymore. I bought this as a 60th b-day present to myself. I knew I did not want to go super cheap so I chose this one after doing some research, expensive is not always better, and it seemed reasonably priced as compared to most.
    So here is the good and bad.
    Positives:
    1) Reasonably priced
    2) Pretty tough and durable. The reason I have not worn a watch for over 30 years was I tended to destroy them.
    3) Easy to charge

    The Negatives:
    1) The battery life is not what it was advertised as. I get about 3 weeks out of a charge. Advertised at 60 days
    2) It has trouble maintaining a connection and synch to my phone. I use a galaxy 21 plus. I have to restart the watch and sometimes my phone to get it to reconnect via Bluetooth.
    3) Once reconnected, It has difficulty synching and can take several minutes once reconnected.
    4) Not a fan of the band have to wear it kind of loose otherwise it pinches and is a little uncomfortable to wear. I find myself messing with it to much. That might be on me because I have not worn a watch in so long.
    5) I spend quite a bit of time traveling and could not find just a charger for the watch, as it requires a specific one by the manufacturer. To take on the road and leave the other at home. That is why I needed a long battery life.
    When it gets down to it would I recommend this watch? Not sure. I purchased it in April 2024 and am still undecided as this was my first one, and I bought it mainly for the health monitoring features. I do not use most of the other features. But the features I do use seem to be good and relatively accurate.

    It has now been almost a year since I purchased this watch. So, I figured I would submit an update.
    I like the watch, but it fails to deliver on the 60+ days on a charge. At best I get about 3 weeks before I have to recharge it, good thing it charges quickly overnight.
    Second downside is the band it comes with is not very good and I am now looking for a metal replacement band.
    Beyond that I recommend the watch good product for reasonable price.

    5) I spend quite a bit of time traveling and could not find just a charger for the watch, as it requires a specific one by the manufacturer. To take on the road and leave the other at home. That is why I needed a long battery life.
    When it gets down to it would I recommend this watch? Not sure. I purchased it in April 2024 and am still undecided as this was my first one, and I bought it mainly for the health monitoring features. I do not use most of the other features. But the features I do use seem to be good and relatively accurate.

    It has now been almost a year since I purchased this watch. So, I figured I would submit an update.
    I like the watch, but it fails to deliver on the 60+ days on a charge. At best I get about 3 weeks before I have to recharge it, good thing it charges quickly overnight.
    Second downside is the band it comes with is not very good and I am now looking for a metal replacement band.
    Beyond that I recommend the watch good product for reasonable price.
